# spark-benchmark

Reproducible local-LLM benchmark harness for **NVIDIA DGX Spark only** (v1).
v1 is intentionally Spark-only — never frame results as cross-platform comparisons.

## v1 lineup (canonical)

- `qwen-3.6` (Ollama tag `qwen3.6:35b`)
- `gemma-4` (Ollama tag `gemma4:31b`)
- `nemotron-3` (Ollama tag `nemotron3:33b`)
- `nemotron-3-super` is **retired** — its YAML is a tombstone, do not re-add it.

The curated lineup above is the *default*. Every CLI surface
(`run` / `console` / `benchmark` / `wizard`) accepts
`--allow-auto-detected` to also offer any non-vision/non-embedding tag
that Ollama reports — those entries are auto-synthesized via
`spark_benchmark.model_registry.synthesize_model_config` and labeled
`auto-detected`. The curses TUI behaves as if the flag were always on.

## Production backend

Ollama HTTP at `http://localhost:11434/api/generate`. `llamacpp` adapter exists; `trt-llm` / `vllm` are stubs.

## Run commands (always with `PYTHONPATH=src`)

```bash
PYTHONPATH=src python3 -m spark_benchmark.cli wizard \
  --experiment configs/experiments/spark-ollama-baseline.yaml --platform spark

PYTHONPATH=src python3 -m spark_benchmark.cli benchmark \
  otestuj qwen gemma nemotron zamer se na rychlost spolehlivost \
  --experiment configs/experiments/spark-ollama-baseline.yaml --platform spark
```

NL parser understands Czech + English keywords (`rychlost`/`speed`,
`spolehliv`/`reliab`, `kod`/`code`, `dlouhodob`/`sustained`, `openclaw`).

## Results layout (do not change shape lightly)

```
results/benchmarks/<run-id>/
├─ plan.json
└─ <suite>/{manifest.json, results.jsonl, summary.json, summary.md}
```

Run IDs come from `results_bundle.make_run_id()` (`YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ-<8hex>`).

## Custom (BYOT) suites

User-supplied benchmark suites live in `spark_benchmark.custom_suites`
and ship under `spark-bench run-custom` / `validate-custom`. v0.2.0
implements **Mode A only** (`mode: quick`, pass-through, no scoring);
`mode: scored` is rejected at load time. v0.2.1 adds a top-level
`Custom` entry to the curses TUI (`spark-bench shell`) — it discovers
suites from `examples/custom-tests/**/suite.yaml` plus prior runs in
`results/custom/<slug>/<run-id>/manifest.json` (helper:
`shell.discover_custom_suites`) and writes manifests with
`source: "shell"` so reporting can tell TUI runs apart from CLI runs.
See `docs/custom-tests-spec.md` for the full schema, run-bundle layout
(`results/custom/<slug>/<run-id>/` with `kind: "custom"` manifest),
and the v0.3+ roadmap. Custom suites are **deliberately separate**
from `suites.SuiteDefinition` — never reuse the canonical schema for
user-facing input.

For full module map see `docs/architecture.md`. For planned canonical
suites see `docs/extensions-spec.md`. Methodology lives in
`METHODOLOGY.md` — keep it honest: publish failures, not just wins.
